29/04/2004
WARSAW, Poland -- Albanian President Alfred Moisiu met separately with his counterparts from Poland, Slovakia and Bulgaria on Wednesday (28 April), on the sidelines of the European Economic Forum in Warsaw.
Talks focused on the situation in the Balkans.
Of particular concern was Kosovo, which Moisiu visited several days ago.
During the meetings, he expressed concern about the instability in Kosovo and pledged that Albania would continue to play a stabilising role in the region.
(PAP, ATA, BTA - 28/04/04)
